replies.msg:
Klopp asked whether VAR disrupted the flow, he interrupts by saying: &quot;Which flow? - I think it's important that we all wanted, if a goal should be disallowed, it's disallowed. After the game we often talk about these decisions.&ldquo;<br />
<br />
Klopp: &rdquo;It's normal that in the game it takes a little longer. That will, I think, become a little bit smoother in the future.&rdquo;

Klopp on Can: &ldquo;Sometimes a player just wants to sit out his contract. That's not cool for the club, but there are moments in which you have to accept it.&ldquo; <br />
<br />
Klopp: &ldquo;And as long as the player behaves like Emre does, then I have absolutely nothing to complain about. He gives everything he has and identifies with the club.&quot;

